(inner) open() → {Document}

Opens the specified document file. If you open a pre-Illustrator 9 document that contains both RGB and CMYK colors and documentColorSpace is supplied, all colors are converted to the specified color space. If the parameter is not supplied, Illustrator opens a dialog so the user can choose the color space.
